biography.bio: Asbjørn Andersen was born on August 30, 1903 in Copenhagen, Denmark as Hans Asbjørn Gammelmark Andersen. He was an actor and director, known for Reptilicus le monstre des mers (1961), Boy of Two Worlds (1959) and Kampen om Næsbygård (1964). He was married to Tove Ulla Høffding Dyrhauge and Nena Conny. He died on December 10, 1978 in Denmark.
biography.name: Asbjørn Andersen

biography.bio: Karen Berg was born on May 28, 1906 in Copenhagen, Denmark as Karen Else Caroline Berg. She was an actress, known for Kampen om Næsbygård (1964), Be Dear to Me (1957) and Huset på Christianshavn (1970). She was married to Svend Gunnar Jørgensen. She died on November 15, 1995 in Charlottenlund, Denmark.
biography.name: Karen Berg

biography.bio: Ole Wisborg was born on August 14, 1925 in Copenhagen, Denmark. He was an actor, known for Caresses interdites (1970), Farlig ungdom (1953) and Kampen om Næsbygård (1964). He was married to Tove Wisborg. He died on December 20, 1978 in Denmark.
biography.name: Ole Wisborg

biography.bio: Poul Reichhardt was born on February 2, 1913 in Ganløse, Denmark as Poul David Reichhardt. He was an actor, known for Huset på Christianshavn (1970), Cafe Paradise (1950) and Soldaten og Jenny (1947). He was married to Charlotte Ernst, Margareta Fahlén and Lili Lani. He died on October 31, 1985 in Denmark.
biography.name: Poul Reichhardt

biography.bio: Inger Stender was born on June 7, 1912 in Copenhagen, Denmark as Inger Margueritha Koefod Stender. She was an actress, known for Frihed forpligter (1951), Krybskytterne på Næsbygård (1966) and Natekspressen P903 (1942). She was married to Mogens Flindt-Larsen. She died on June 26, 1989 in Denmark.
biography.name: Inger Stender

biography.bio: Agnes Rehni was born on May 24, 1887 in Maribo, Denmark. She was an actress, known for Grevindens ære (1919), Støvsugerbanden (1963) and Far til fire med fuld musik (1961). She died on November 3, 1966 in Denmark.
biography.name: Agnes Rehni

biography.bio: Ib Mossin was born on July 3, 1933 in Denmark. He was an actor and director, known for The Son from Vingaarden (1975), Farlig ungdom (1953) and Kampen om Næsbygård (1964). He was married to Anne-Marie Juhl. He died on December 21, 2004 in Copenhagen, Denmark.
biography.name: Ib Mossin

biography.bio: Jane Thomsen was born on April 14, 1939 in Denmark. She is an actress, known for The Red Horses (1968), Næsbygårds arving (1965) and Krybskytterne på Næsbygård (1966).
biography.name: Jane Thomsen

biography.bio: Ole Neumann was born on October 16, 1947 in Copenhagen, Denmark. He is an actor, known for Father of Four (1953), Næsbygårds arving (1965) and Far til fire i sneen (1954).
biography.name: Ole Neumann

biography.bio: Helga Frier was born on June 12, 1893. She was an actress, known for Fløjtespilleren (1953), Naar bønder elsker (1942) and Hvor går Karl hen? (1957). She died on January 9, 1972 in Denmark.
biography.name: Helga Frier

biography.bio: Marie-Louise Coninck was born on December 8, 1936. She is an actress, known for After the Wedding (2006), Department Q: The Keeper of Lost Causes (2013) and The Shooter (2013). She is married to Baard Owe. They have four children.
biography.name: Marie-Louise Coninck

biography.bio: Einar Juhl was born on April 8, 1896 in Denmark. He was an actor, known for Vejrhanen (1952), Far til fire i byen (1956) and Adam og Eva (1953). He died on June 1, 1982 in Denmark.
biography.name: Einar Juhl

biography.bio: Knud Schrøder was born on July 28, 1903 in Denmark. He was an actor, known for Far til fire i byen (1956), Cafe Paradise (1950) and Little Dorrit (1924). He died on December 15, 1976 in Denmark.
biography.name: Knud Schrøder

biography.bio: Holger Vistisen was born on June 13, 1932 in Copenhagen, Denmark. He was an actor and casting director, known for Orion's Belt (1985), L'espoir aux trousses (1989) and Ti slips og et hjerte (1967). He died on February 13, 2007.
biography.name: Holger Vistisen

biography.bio: Yvonne Ekmann was born on February 8, 1945 in Denmark. She is an actress, known for Soldaterkammerater på bjørnetjeneste (1968), Kampen om Næsbygård (1964) and Days in My Father's House (1968).
biography.name: Yvonne Ekmann
